name: Cooper Bedin
details: I'm a senior majoring in linguistics and computer science, with a special interest in queer and trans language and self-expression in linguistics. I also do lots of tech theater with the student group BareStage and spend lots of time hanging out with my cat, Jellybean.

name: Ruslana Yurtyn
details: I'm a junior studying computer science. I love knitting and dancing, and I'm the President of the Association of Women in EE&CS

name: Jennifer Huang
details: I’m a senior studying CS/Math/Music. In my free time I like playing video games, cooking, hunting down newest boba shops, and singing to Korean HipHop. Nice to meet you all!

name: Lukas Chang
details: Hi everyone I'm Lukas, a 3rd year CS major from the South Bay Area. In my free time I love listening to music and producing music on Ableton. I hope I can share my love for CS with you all!

name: Rosalie Fang
details: Hi y'all! I'm Rosalie, a junior majoring CS and Econ, and minoring in Physics. I'm TA-ing for 61C which in my opinion is (one of) the best class on campus. I love traveling, eating good food, and have an (un)healthy addiction for boba. My trivial fact is that I have watched the entire LOTR trilogy more than 20 times.

name: Maxwell Chen
details: Hi! I'm Maxwell, a senior studying Computer Science from San Jose, CA. I'm broadly interested in machine learning, signal processing, and neuroscience. Outside of academics, I'm passionate about UI/UX design, music production, and generative art. Looking forward to a great (last) semester!

name: Noor Mahini
details: Hello there! My name is Noor and I'm a 3rd year EECS major from Berkeley. In my free time, I enjoy playing video games, tennis, viola, and piano. I also like anime and Marvel, so feel free to talk to me about those! This is my 3rd semester in CSM and I'm super excited to meet you all!

name: Alec Li
details: Hi! My name is Alec and I'm a sophomore CS and Applied Math double major. I enjoy composing music as a hobby, and I spend way too much time typesetting in LaTeX and doing random coding projects.

name: Simon Tsui
details: Hello! I am a junior studying Computer Science and Statistics. Feel free to reach out to me if you want to talk about classes at Berkeley, food recs, or anything else. Looking forward to a great CS 88 experience this semester!

name: Ryan Nuqui
details:
hi y'all!
I'm ryan and I'm a fifth year studying cs & applied math. this will be my eighth semester of CSM and I'm really excited to get the opportunity to meet and mentor more folks :) talk to me if you're fond of ducks, trying out new restaurants (try Rose Pizzeria!), or if you have any questions about anything. looking forward to meeting you!
